parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle seals can cause leakage of lubricant, leading to premature wear of the axle bearings and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Oil or lubricant leakage from the front axle
grinding or noise from the front wheels
vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seals can cause leakage of lubricant, leading to premature wear of the axle bearings and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Oil or lubricant leakage from the rear axle
grinding or noise from the rear wheels
vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel cylinder boots can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to reduced braking performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leakage from the rear wheels
spongy brake pedal
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause poor visibility during rain, snow, or other weather conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers do not turn on
windshield wipers move slowly or erratically
windshield wipers leave streaks or residue on the windshield
windshield wipers do not clear water or debris effectively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ventilation fan can cause discomfort, distraction, and decreased visibility due to fogging or misting of the windshield, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vent fan does not turn on
vent fan is noisy or vibrating
vent fan blows cold or hot air intermittently
vent fan does not circulate air properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear drum brakes can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Rear drums failed
brakes leaking
noise when applying the brakes
spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake fluid leak can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leak
noise when applying the brakes
spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering system fails to operate
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
